# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the React + Vite project following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0`
- **Method**: Installed via npm (npm install @vercel/speed-insights)
- **Lockfile**: Updated package-lock.json to ensure consistent dependency resolution

### 2. Code Integration
**Modified File**: `client/src/App.jsx`

**Changes**:
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component in the AppContent component
- Maintained existing code structure and followed the project's pattern of placing analytics components together

### 3. Verification Steps Completed
✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✅ No new linting errors introduced by the changes
✅ Package.json updated with the new dependency
✅ Package-lock.json properly updated for dependency consistency
✅ Changes staged for commit

## Implementation Details

The Speed Insights component was added following the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects:
- Fetched latest instructions from: https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Framework identified: React + Vite
- Package manager: npm
- Integration point: Root App.jsx component
- Placement: Added after the Analytics component in the AppContent function

The implementation follows the same pattern as the existing Vercel Analytics integration, ensuring consistency with the project's architecture.

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Speed Insights will automatically start collecting performance metrics
2. Metrics can be viewed in the Vercel dashboard under Speed Insights
3. The tracking script will be automatically injected by Vercel's platform

